<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine Service, Model Year 1994 - 1998 - TURBOCHARGER - Installation -
        High Torque Wastegated Turbocharger
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="5">
        <title>High Torque Wastegated Turbocharger</title>
        <figure id="f1200239" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg3/EG3303.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="328px"
                     scalefitheight="472px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Turbocharger Oil Supply O-Ring and Oil Drain O-Ring</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil Supply O-Ring</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil Drain O-Ring</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger Mounting Pad</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply a light coat of grease to a new oil drain O-ring and oil supply O-ring. Install the
                O-rings into the turbocharger mounting pad.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the turbocharger pedestal on the crankcase. Tighten the pedestal mounting bolts to
                the standard torque value.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1200275" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg6/EG6414.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Turbocharger Exhaust Tube Mounting Hardware (Right Side Shown)</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Right Exhaust Tube</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Exhaust Tube Mounting Nut</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Right Exhaust Manifold</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Exhaust Tube Mounting Bolt</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the turbocharger exhaust tubes to the exhaust manifolds. Finger tighten the mounting
                hardware.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a new the oil supply O-ring and oil drain O-ring on the top of the pedestal.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1200276" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg6/EG6430.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Turbocharger Connection Points</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Exhaust Inlet Clamp</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Exhaust Inlet Adapter</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger Mounting Bolt (2)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the turbocharger on the pedestal. Install the mounting bolts and tighten them to the
                special torque valve.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the seal and align the exhaust inlet adapter with the turbine inlet. Install the
                clamp and tighten it to the special torque value.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten the mounting hardware at the exhaust manifolds to the standard torque value.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1200277" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg9/EG9128.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="328px"
                     scalefitheight="472px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Installing the Charge Air Cooling Tube/Crossover Pipe Assembly</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Crossover Pipe</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Charge Air Cooling Tube</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Hose Clamps</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger Intake Manifold Hoses</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger Compressor Outlet Seal</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger Compressor Outlet Clamp</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use clean engine oil to lubricate a new turbocharger compressor outlet seal. Install the
                seal into the compressor housing.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the charge air cooling tube/crossover pipe assembly as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Install the charge air cooling tube/crossover pipe assembly to the turbocharger
                    compressor housing and intake manifold hoses.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Tighten the four hose clamps (two per side) to secure the intake manifold hoses to the
                    air intake manifold covers.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">To secure the charge air cooling tube to the turbocharger compressor housing, tighten
                    the turbocharger compressor outlet clamp.
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f120024" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figEG7/EG7404.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Installing the Road Draft Tube</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Road Draft Tube</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Road Draft Tube Mounting Bolts</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Crankcase Breather</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Air Inlet Elbow</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the air inlet elbow and clamp. Tighten the clamp.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the road draft tube and mounting bolts on the crankcase. Tighten the bolts to the
                standard torque.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect the road draft tube to the crankcase breather. Install and tighten the hose clamp.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
